==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxalan
<hw>Ox"a*lan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Alloxan</er>, by transposition of letters.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A complex nitrogenous substance <chform>C3N3H5O3</chform> obtained
from alloxan (or when urea is fused with ethyl oxamate), as a stable
white crystalline powder; -- called also
<altname>oxaluramide</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxalantin</ent>⟦br⟧
